					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I don't think I have any suggestions for improving your routine, since a lot of game aspects have influence over this kind of thing. I just thought the times you mentioned sounded bad, but then again this is a complex process due to the flipping, clipping of parts that are off screen and even OAM cycling, so it might not be as slow as I first thought it was. Mine is fairly slow too, but I don't have any numbers.</div>
<br />I use the virtuanes referred here: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=5836">http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=5836</a><!-- m -->
<br />To check routines time, it's really useful.
<br />You only have to write to a register to start counting and write to another to stop the count.</div>

